A great sequel to its predecessors. I found it uncompelling at first, but I think I enjoyed this one the most. The characters all seemed richer and the post-game was far more fulfilling. The magic mediums were a little bizarre, but I valued them for specific needs in the end. I also didn't notice any annoying enemy scaling to punish my investments, either. Some of the translations need work, but most of it is good enough. Finally, cheesy romance was minimal, thank goodness.
I hope the dev will make another sequel. This game is one of the game that I would like to keep playing. Definitely one of my favorite.

It was a fun game, but felt like the item management/crafting/spell menus could have been improved. I really like to sort and filter items things. Spells could have been grouped by level/type (summon/fire/lightning/ice) items and crafting allow for favoriting certain crafts and locking items from being used and or sold. Would have enjoyed having a cap on item/training and or diminishing returns on stat improvements. I would go and buy a ton of boar meat to make life in the beginning.
